                <head>No. 583.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lothrop</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-03-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 12, 1887</date>. (Received April
                        1.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 101.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: A letter received this morning from Mr. Heenan,
                    consul at Odessa, informs me that Abraham Thiessen “is slowly making his way <pb
                        facs="1048" n="954" xml:id="pg_954"/> to Odessa, and is expected there in a
                    few days.” The cause of this slow movement is not known.</p>
                <p>Very truly, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George V. N. Lothrop.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. S.—March</hi> 13. Mr. Heenan telegraphs this
                        morning, “Thiessen sent to Constantinople to-day.”</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>G. V. N. L.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
